  "overview": "An update for Oracle Linux is now available for Oracle Linux 10.",
  "description": "[6.3.7-5.0.2]\n- Backports various pcp bugs and enhancements  [Orabug: 35778072]\n- [Orabug: 36932629] [Orabug: 37655753] [Orabug: 38435551]\n- [Orabug: 38380185] [Orabug: 38526634]\n\n[6.3.7-5.0.1]\n- Fixes build issues due to patch 1002 applying error [Orabug: 38288886]\n- Add support for rocestat pmda [Orabug: 38109270]\n- Add support for rocestat client [Orabug: 38109292]\n\n[6.3.7-5]\n- Make pcp-zeroconf start enabled services once again (RHEL-93182)\n- Fix python PMDA wrapper handling of list objects\n- Improve tmpfiles.d handling of empty directories\n- Backport some more fixes to the OpenMetrics PMDA\n- Fix a multilib regression in PCP header files\n\n[6.3.7-4]\n- Backport metric removal for pmdaopenmetrics\n\n[6.3.7-3]\n- Backport the webapi filtering fix to allow the use of exact matching. (RHEL-88201)\n\n[6.3.7-2]\n- Add selinux policy for new proc_psi_t-induced failure",
